President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Rebecca Kelly Slaughter as a Member of the Federal Trade Commission. Slaughter is currently the chief counsel to Senator Charles Schumer of New York. She has been advising Senator Schumer on legal, competition, telecom, privacy, consumer protection, and intellectual property matters since 2009. Prior to joining Senator Schumer's office, Slaughter worked as an associate in the D.C. office of Sidley Austin LLP. She holds a B.A. in Anthropology magna cum laude from Yale University and a J.D. from Yale Law School.

Additionally, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint Julie E. Cram as the Senior Coordinator of United States International Basic Education Assistance. Cram is currently the Deputy Assistant Administrator in the Bureau for Economic Growth, Education and Environment (E3). Her responsibilities include overseeing the development and implementation of USAID's strategy and policies in the education sector. Cram has over 18 years of experience in issue advocacy, communications, and government affairs. She previously served as Deputy Assistant to President and Director of Public Liaison for President George W. Bush from 2007-2009.